  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm not sure about the two buttons at the bottom. Whatever filters I modify, it's taken into account instantly. It means there's nothing to \"save\". It's kind of already saved. Intead of \"Save and close\", it should be just \"Close\" IMO.\r\nIf there should be a \"save\" button, I think it should work like this:\r\n- Filter A is applied.\r\n- User opens up the filter popup.\r\n- User applies Filter B.\r\n- User doesn't clicks \"save\" button but \"close\" button.\r\n- The only filter applied now is still A.\r\n\r\nAccording to current behaviors of our widgets, \"reset\" and \"close\" buttons seem to be enough. What do you think?",
